        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-03-26 17:48:42.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> > Patch Set 2:\n> > \n> > > Patch Set 2:\n> > > \n> > > I mean, check \"usage\" of default constructor. As I can see, none of them are used.\n> > Yes,you're right but most of them required for tests with com.google.code.beanmatchers.BeanMatchers#hasValidGettersAndSetters and com.google.code.beanmatchers.BeanMatchers#hasValidBeanConstructor\n> > Either we need to reconsider its usage or let default constructors used only for tests.\n> > What do you think about it?\n> \n> IMPO, If default constructor used ONLY in test, it should be removed, by fixing tests. Same for hasValidGettersAndSetters. No reasons to test LOMBOK Getter/Setter.\n> As reference you can use https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/sdc/+/104500\n\nI've removed default constructors used only for tests and also removed those test. Thank you.",
        "patchset_number": 2
